Commentary Text: McClenaghan to Narine, out Lbw!! Dead straight. Just that it goes onto the pad after smashing the bat. A yorker on the stumps, quite where he should have been right from the start. Commentary Text: Krunal Pandya to Uthappa, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! Two wickets in the over. Uthappa falls cheaply. This was floated up much fuller from KP, tempting Uthappa to go for the big shot. The Karnataka batsman went after it, albeit didn't find the sweet spot in his willow. Commentary Text: Narine to Rohit, out Lbw!! Rohit is not walking. He's not pleased with the decision. Has some choice words to say to umpire Nandan. "That's an absolute shocker," says KP on air and he's right. Massive inside edge onto the pad. Two poor decisions in two overs might have just cost MI the game. The off-break which turns back in and cramps Rohit for room, he hurriedly brings his bat down and smashes it into his pads. The umpire didn't spot it and gave it out after a thought. Rohit was fuming after the decision. Even showed his bat to the umpire gesturing he hit it. But you can't overturn an onfield decision unless you have the DRS and that is not available in the IPL. This wicket has to be the game changing moment. Rohit lbw b Narine 2(6)

Commentary Text: Woakes to Buttler, 2 runs, Lynn is holding his arm and walking off. KKR fans you don't have to read what is coming up next. Fuller and just outside off, Buttler goes for the loft down the ground, toe-ends it over mid-off. Lynn backtracks and dives full length, almost got a fingertip to the ball, but the main part is that he landed badly and did not even get up to retrieve the ball which stopped inside the rope. It was his left shoulder. Meanwhile, the batsmen only run a couple of runs. They had a chance to run four, but the pair showed good sportsmanship. Lynn straightaway called for the physio. He knew that something serious had happened
